com.github.sanity4j.util

Interface StartElementListener


  • public interface StartElementListener
    StartElementListener - listener interface called by JaxbMarshaller when iterating through an XML document. This allows readers to unmarshall sections of the large documents that would otherwise consume excess amounts of memory.
    Since:
    Sanity4J 1.0
    Author:
    Yiannis Paschalidis

      • foundElement

                  javax.xml.stream.XMLEventReader reader,
                  javax.xml.bind.Unmarshaller unmarshaller)
           throws javax.xml.bind.JAXBException
        Called whenever a start element is encountered during traversal of an XML document.
        Parameters:
        element - the start element which was found
        reader - the XML event reader that is in use
        unmarshaller - the current JAXB unmarshaller in use.
        Throws:
        javax.xml.bind.JAXBException - if there is an error during unmarshalling.
